            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, reduce the heat to medium-high and add the<strong> sliced red onion</strong> with a splash of <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for an initial 6-7 min or until browned</p><p>After the initial 6-7 min, remove the lid and cook for a final 2-3 min or until the liquid in the pan has evaporated and the koftes are cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Ordered extra halloumi? Slice and cook in a pan with a little oil for 4-6 min or until golden all over</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
